comment: How does it sound at lower volumes? Does it stay consistent throughout the volumes? One thing I hate is when a speaker sounds one way at 30%, and then like a completely different speaker at 80%. I get they do this to maximum volume or whatever, but it's always been a trait I hate and a lot of speakers seem to be doing it these days. JBL is one the worse.. banging solid bass at lower volumes, then at higher volumes it becomes a crap speaker with no bass.

author: @xirruz
comment:
Actually prefer the Motion+ to a JBL Flip, on 30Watt line-up it's unbeatable imho. 

My actual list is this though:

10-15Watts - Tribit Stormbox Micro/Bose Soundlink Flex
30-50Watts - Soundcore Motion+/Bose Soundlink Max/Sony SRS-XB33
80-100Watts - Tribit Stormbox Lava/Tribit Stormbox Blast 1/Sony SRS-XB100

The only speaker out of all of those I keep reaching for when I go out is the Soundcore Motion+, occasionally the Tribit Stormbox Micro when I need something smaller.

I just tend to stay away from JBL as they're overpriced where I'm from, like the JBL Flip 6 is around 120$ and the Motion+ is around 70$ the price disparity is mind boggling. I'd rather just go for the 'budget' option or just buy from a known/reputable audio equipment brand/manufacturer, like I'd rather buy Harman Kardon's than JBL's at the price they're at.
